on alfred_script(q)
tell application "Finder" if exists Finder window 1 then set pathList to (quoted form of POSIX path of (folder of the front window as alias)) else set pathList to "desktop" end if set command to "clear && cd " & pathList end tell
tell application "System Events" -- some versions might identify as "iTerm2" instead of "iTerm" set isRunning to (exists (processes where name is "iTerm")) or (exists (processes where name is "iTerm2")) end tell
tell application "iTerm" activate set hasNoWindows to ((count of windows) is 0) if isRunning and hasNoWindows then create window with default profile end if select first window
tell the first window tell current session to write text command end tell end tell
end alfred_script
on alfred_script(q) tell application "System Events" keystroke "j" using (command down, option down) end tell end alfred_script
on alfred_script(q) tell application "System Events" keystroke "," using command down end tell end alfred_script

on alfred_script(q)
tell application "Finder" if exists Finder window 1 then make new file at (target of front Finder window as text) with properties {name:q} else make new file at (path to desktop) with properties {name:q} end if end tell
end alfred_script

query=$1
# 目标路径 dir_path=${query} # 重命名序号 num=1 # 存放目录 newDir="rename_dir" # 如果目录不存在，创建一个新的文件夹 [[ ! -d ${dir_path}/${newDir} ]] && mkdir ${dir_path}/${newDir} for file in $dir_path/*; do # 如果是目录，不进行重命名 if [[ -d $file ]]; then continue fi # 获取文件mime类型 mime=${file##*.} # 新路径 newPath=${file%/*}/$newDir # 文件后缀如果大于6，则表示不是一个mime类型，直接回填文件名 if [[ "${#mime}" -gt 6 ]]; then cp -f ${file} $newPath/$num # 如果是一个mime类型，则转换 else rename=${num}.${mime} cp -f ${file} $newPath/$rename fi num=$((num+1)) done
on alfred_script(q) tell application "Finder" empty the trash end tell end alfred_script

on alfred_script(q) tell application "Finder" if exists Finder window 1 then set pathList to (quoted form of POSIX path of (folder of the front window as alias)) else set pathList to "desktop" end if set command to "clear && cd " & pathList end tell
tell application "System Events" -- some versions might identify as "iTerm2" instead of "iTerm" set isRunning to (exists (processes where name is "iTerm")) or (exists (processes where name is "iTerm2")) end tell tell application "iTerm" activate set hasNoWindows to ((count of windows) is 0) if isRunning and hasNoWindows then create window with default profile end if select first window tell the first window tell current session to write text command tell application "System Events" delay 1.5 keystroke "code ." key code 76 delay 0.5 keystroke "w" using command down end tell end tell end tell end alfred_script
on alfred_script(q) tell application "System Events" keystroke "v" using command down end tell end alfred_script

on alfred_script(q) tell application "Microsoft Edge" set URi to (get URL of active tab of window 1) set the clipboard to URi tell application "System Events" keystroke "N" using {command down, shift down} keystroke "V" using command down key code 76 end tell end tell end alfred_script

on alfred_script(q) tell application "System Events" keystroke "c" using (command down, option down) end tell end alfred_script

on alfred_script(q) tell application "Google Chrome" set URi to (get URL of active tab of window 1) set the clipboard to URi tell application "System Events" keystroke "N" using {command down, shift down} keystroke "V" using command down key code 76 end tell end tell end alfred_script
